    "updated_at": "2016-08-29T23:45:34Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I know the game itself doesn't have any performance degrade on it, but extra performance is always a good thing.\n\nI guess what I am trying to say is I would like to see stuff that new(er) OpenGL versions offered that aren't in the game already, like for example, enhancements to shaders, tessellations (don't know if it would be noticeable in OpenRA, but still nice to know you have the option and all), improved rendering features, better textures.\n\nAs far as hardware is concerned, I mean OpenGL runs as far back as HD 5000 series (7000 series for 4.5) for AMD and Nvidia GeForce 400 series and those are 1gb cards (these are OpenGL 4.5 specs). I mean, to run Windows just find (well at least since Windows 7 to Windows 10), you basically need a 1gb card and all.\n"
